Ben Johnson disqualified from the 1988 Summer Olympics suffered minor
injuries in a fight involving five men in a swank district of Toronto.
Johnson, driving his mothers' car, slowed for pedestrians who then
banged on the car.  Johnson got out to challenge the men one of whom
punched Johnson and kicked in the windshield of the car causing $700
damage.  Johnson chased and caught the man and held him until police
arrived.  Johnson's companions, other Canadian athletes, chased the
other suspects but they got away.  Johnson's lawyer said that the men
knew it was Johnson in the car.</SUM>
